# First-party plugins are no longer distributed via the kelvinclaw-plugins index.
# They are built from source in plugins/ and baked into the Docker runtime image at
# docker/Dockerfile.runtime (plugin-builder stage → /opt/kelvin/plugins-builtin/).
#
# kelvin.cli is vendored as a pre-built tarball at release/vendor/kelvin.cli-0.1.2.tar.gz
# and installed by scripts/kelvin-setup.sh at container init time.
#
# To add or update a first-party plugin:
#   1. Edit source in plugins/<plugin-name>/
#   2. Run plugins/<plugin-name>/build.sh to rebuild payload/plugin.wasm
#   3. docker compose up --build   (plugin-builder stage recompiles on change)
